<subSubSection id="C31CD2F88E608041A0B1A372FC3A3888" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB981738E608041A0B1A372FC3A3888" blockId="3.[151,1437,381,1511]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A0B1A372FED338E7" bold="true" box="[151,273,381,406]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E608041A13AA372FDCA38E7" authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[284,520,381,406]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="electrinus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A13AA372FDCA38E7" box="[284,520,381,406]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Drephalys electrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A241E01A8E608041A235A372FD9438E7" box="[531,598,381,406]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A235A372FD9438E7" bold="true" box="[531,598,381,406]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E608041A2D0A371FB2938E7" authority="(Mabille &amp; Boullet, 1919)" authorityName="Mabille &amp; Boullet" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="Mabille &amp; Boullet" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[758,1259,381,406]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoenicoides">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A2D0A371FC7238E7" box="[758,944,381,406]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. phoenicoides</emphasis>
(Mabille &amp; Boullet, 1919)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E608041A50EA372FF3938C6" authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dracarys" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A50EA372FF3938C6" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Drephalys dracarys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A241E01A8E608041A127A391FE8338C6" box="[257,321,414,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A127A391FE8338C6" bold="true" box="[257,321,414,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in wing markings and in the width of the white transversal band on ventral hind wings but it can be distinguished by the following male genitalia characters: costa of valva without a projection (
<figureCitation id="133D9DF68E608041A494A3B0FB3738A9" box="[1202,1269,447,472]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1161,1184]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,199,1143]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1437,199,1143]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. Male genitalia of Drephalys species. Tegumen, uncus, gnathos and saccus in lateral view; right valva in left, right and dorsal views; tegumen and uncus in dorsal view; aedeagus in left lateral and dorsal views; detail of the everted cornuti. 7. D. dracarys sp. n., 8. D. electrinus sp. n., 9. D. citrinus sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1440353/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) and aedeagus with the third distal margin serrated and without a spine-like process (
<figureCitation id="133D9DF68E608041A380A3EEFC283888" box="[934,1002,481,506]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1161,1184]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,199,1143]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1437,199,1143]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. Male genitalia of Drephalys species. Tegumen, uncus, gnathos and saccus in lateral view; right valva in left, right and dorsal views; tegumen and uncus in dorsal view; aedeagus in left lateral and dorsal views; detail of the everted cornuti. 7. D. dracarys sp. n., 8. D. electrinus sp. n., 9. D. citrinus sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1440353/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31CD2F88E608041A0E1A00DFAE73AC0" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB981738E608041A0E1A00DFAE73AC0" blockId="3.[151,1437,381,1511]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A0E1A00DFE583B6A" bold="true" box="[199,410,514,539]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Description, male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A18FA00DFE273B6A" box="[425,485,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Head</emphasis>
: antenna with yellow scales at the base of each segment ventrally; basal half of the ventral club yellow, nudum of 36 segments (n=2). 
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A2ECA02BFCDA3B4C" box="[714,792,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Thorax</emphasis>
: as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E608041A343A02AFC2B3B4C" authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[869,1001,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dracarys" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A343A02AFC2B3B4C" box="[869,1001,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. dracarys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A241E01A8E608041A3D4A02BFBF23B4C" box="[1010,1072,548,573]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A3D4A02BFBF23B4C" bold="true" box="[1010,1072,548,573]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A41FA02AFAE63B4C" box="[1081,1316,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Forewing, upper side</emphasis>
: length 
<quantity id="4CFE2C968E608041A5A7A02BFF073B2C" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" unit="mm" value="21.0">21 mm</quantity>
; costal fold short; dark yellow patch covers the basal third of the costal margin; one small circular yellow spot in CuA2-2A, aligned to the proximal hyaline spot of discal cell; three apical hyaline spots in R3-R4, R4-R5, and R5-M1 more aligned with each other than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E608041A1DAA083FD423BD2" authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[508,640,650,675]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dracarys" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A1DAA083FD423BD2" box="[508,640,650,675]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. dracarys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A241E01A8E608041A2ACA085FD0B3BD2" box="[650,713,650,675]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A2ACA085FD0B3BD2" bold="true" box="[650,713,650,675]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E608041A322A083FA8E3BD2" authority="Madruga, Siewert, Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[772,1356,650,675]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrinus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A322A083FCB83BD2" box="[772,890,652,675]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. citrinus</emphasis>
Madruga, Siewert, Mielke &amp; Casagrande
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A241E01A8E608041A570A085FA573BD2" box="[1366,1429,650,675]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A570A085FA573BD2" bold="true" box="[1366,1429,650,675]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
. 
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A0B1A0A2FEB93BB4" box="[151,379,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Forewing, underside</emphasis>
: similar to the upper side, except for lighter colors. 
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A3EFA0A3FB003BB4" box="[969,1218,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Hind wing, upper side</emphasis>
: ground color dark brown; all yellow spots with a greenish aspect; large yellow spot on the end of discal cell extending proximally over M; yellow spot in the inferior half of CuA2-2A extending proximally over 2A; fringes yellow. 
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A444A0E1FA893A76" box="[1122,1355,750,775]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Hind wing, underside</emphasis>
: tornus with a dark brown patch; anal margin cream with a short white patch in 3A-anal margin. 
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A449A11CFB173A5D" box="[1135,1237,787,812]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="133D9DF68E608041A4C3A11CFAE53A5A" box="[1253,1319,787,812]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1161,1184]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,199,1143]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1437,199,1143]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. Male genitalia of Drephalys species. Tegumen, uncus, gnathos and saccus in lateral view; right valva in left, right and dorsal views; tegumen and uncus in dorsal view; aedeagus in left lateral and dorsal views; detail of the everted cornuti. 7. D. dracarys sp. n., 8. D. electrinus sp. n., 9. D. citrinus sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1440353/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
): tegumen rectangular, extended laterally near the insertion with uncus. Uncus bifid, “U”-shaped; arms as long as the half length of uncus. Valva rectangular, little longer than tegumen+uncus; costa without projection; ampulla with a smooth hook-like process, strongly curved inward and anteriorly; harpe not projected distally. Aedeagus as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C06FAF08E608041A451A177FB3A3AFE" authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[1143,1272,886,911]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dracarys" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9725D618E608041A451A177FB3A3AFE" box="[1143,1272,886,911]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. dracarys</emphasis>
